#Text=The Raveonettes on love , death , desire and war
#Text=Tuesday , October 16 , 2007
#Text=" We 're only two days in and we 're already fucking tired , " says Sune Rose Wagner to David Shankbone as he walks into the dressing room at the Bowery Ballroom .

#Text=Wagner and Sharin Foo comprise the Raveonettes , a group made for " nostalgists who long for Everly Brothers 45 's and diner jukeboxes , the Raveonettes tweak " American Graffiti"-era rock with fuzzed-out surf-guitar riffs , " said The New York Times .

#Text= Few albums provoke such amazing imagery , " said the BBC .

column1: #Text=" Pretty in Black is virtually fuzz-free , " said Rolling Stone of their next album , " highlighting the exquisite detail in the Raveonettes ' gift for pastiche : the prowling , garage-surf guitars in Love in a Trashcan ; the ghost dance of Red Tan , wrapped in Phil Spector-style sleigh bells . "

#Text=Of their current album , Lust Lust Lust , set to be released on November 5th ( although Amazon says March 4 , 2008 ) , Sune told NME that , " There are a lot of songs that deal with desire , restlessness and the tough choices you have to make sometimes . "

column1: #Text=Fans can hear some of the new material at MySpace.com/TheRaveonettes .
#Text=Below is Wikinews reporter David Shankbone 's interview with Sune Rose Wagner and Sharin Foo .
#Text=On influences
#Text=Sune Rose Wagner : Would you like something to drink ?
#Text=David Shankbone : No , I drank so much green tea today I am worried I am going to need to pee throughout the interview .
#Text=At least you 're peeing healthy .
#Text=Can you mix vodka with green tea ?
#Text=I used to .
#Text=How is the tour going ?
#Text=It 's good .
#Text=We 're only two days in and we 're already fucking tired .
#Text=But we 're in great spirits here .
#Text=We 're leaving town tomorrow ...
#Text=we 're happy .
#Text=You guys played in Southpaw right ; how was that ?
#Text=It was beautiful .
#Text=I love that place .
#Text=We played Maxwell 's last night , which is my favorite place .
#Text=This interview may be something different than you guys are used to , because although the questions will be about your music , they will be more about the both of you .
#Text=They are surveys of the landscape .
#Text=For instance , in the last week I have interviews the proprietors and mistresses of an S&M dungeon ;
#Text=Evangelical Christian Presidential candidate Sam Brownback , the President of the ACLU , Augusten Burroughs , and the High Priest of the Church of Satan , and now you .
